<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="186" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,335,614]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">
<bibRefCitation author="Schumann, K." box="[136,336,335,362]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" pagination="117 - 200" refId="ref8376" refString="Schumann, K. (1886) Tilliaceae. Flora Brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas 12 (3): 117 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="journal article" year="1886">Schumann (1886)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[457,717,335,362]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="uniflora" variety="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[457,576,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">L. uniflora</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[631,717,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<emphasis box="[829,963,335,362]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">
<collectorName box="[829,901,335,361]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Riedel</collectorName>
1397
</emphasis>
, and several duplicates are kept in different herbaria. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[246,404,371,398]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" pagination="83 - 84" refId="ref7362" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1980) Consideracoes sobre Luehea candicans Mart. (Tiliaceae), uma nova combinacao - Luehea candicans var. gracilis (Schum.) M. C. S. Cunha. Bradea, Boletim do Herbarium Bradeanum 3 (11): 83 - 84." type="journal article" year="1980">
<collectingCountry box="[246,319,371,397]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1980)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated this collection from 
<collectorName box="[766,923,371,398]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Herbarium M</collectorName>
as the ‘holotype’, but this specimen was not found (
<collectorName box="[219,317,408,434]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">H. Esser</collectorName>
, pers. comm.). 
<collectorName box="[494,556,407,433]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Since</collectorName>
<bibRefCitation author="Schumann, K." box="[564,766,407,434]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" pagination="117 - 200" refId="ref8376" refString="Schumann, K. (1886) Tilliaceae. Flora Brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas 12 (3): 117 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="journal article" year="1886">Schumann (1886)</bibRefCitation>
did not specify any herbarium and since we have not found any specimen in 
<collectorName box="[338,489,443,470]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Herbarium B</collectorName>
where he worked (
<bibRefCitation author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[721,995,443,470]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" refId="ref8497" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976 - 1988) Taxonomic Literature: A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., Smithsonian Libraries, last updated 28 Jun. 2012. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48631" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
–1988: 400), we designate 
<emphasis box="[1313,1451,443,470]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">
<collectorName box="[1313,1385,443,469]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Riedel</collectorName>
1397
</emphasis>
(P 
<date box="[159,275,480,506]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" value="2949-02-14">
<collectingDate box="[159,275,480,506]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" value="2949-02-14">02142949</collectingDate>
</date>
) as the 
<typeStatus box="[364,467,479,505]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[505,769,479,506]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="uniflora" variety="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[505,626,479,505]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">L. uniflora</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[683,769,479,505]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, according to Art. 9.3 of the ICN. It was chosen as the most representative, complete, and best-preserved specimen congruent with the protologue’s description. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[1253,1407,515,542]" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" pagination="83 - 84" refId="ref7362" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1980) Consideracoes sobre Luehea candicans Mart. (Tiliaceae), uma nova combinacao - Luehea candicans var. gracilis (Schum.) M. C. S. Cunha. Bradea, Boletim do Herbarium Bradeanum 3 (11): 83 - 84." type="journal article" year="1980">
<collectingCountry box="[1253,1326,515,541]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1980)
</bibRefCitation>
has restored the nomenclatural priority, recombining 
<taxonomicName box="[681,938,551,578]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="uniflora" variety="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[681,799,551,577]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">L. uniflora</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[852,938,551,577]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1254,551,578]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="candicans" variety="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[973,1116,551,577]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">L. candicans</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1168,1254,551,577]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="186">gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We confirm here the application of this name.
</paragraph>
